When a streaming resume attempt fails with HTTP 409 (checkpoint mismatch) on a long-term basis, the server returns an error payload that includes the following JSON schema:

```json
{
    "error_code": "RESUME_MISMATCH",
    "message": "Checkpoint mismatch. The request is not allowed because it has been modified since the last resume.",
    "details": {
        "request_id": "example_request_id",
        "resume_cursor": "example_resume_cursor"
    },
    "kv_crc": "computed_value"
}
```

The `kv_crc` value inside v2 resume tokens is computed using a specific algorithm. The exact details of the computation are not provided in the given contexts, but it involves hashing and verifying checksums to ensure data integrity across multiple replicas or nodes. This helps prevent replay attacks and ensures that only valid, non-mismatched resumes can be processed by the server.
